04876nam a22006855i 9780824862572DE-B159720210729020517.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210729t20022002hiu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808248625727 a10.1515/97808248625722doi  a(DE-B1597)484641  a(OCoLC)52841085  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ahiucUS-HI 4aDS741.65b.P55 2002eb 7aHIS0080002bisacsh04a9312211 aPines, Yuri, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aFoundations of Confucian Thought :bIntellectual Life in the Chunqiu Period, 722-453 B.C.E. /cYuri Pines. 1aHonolulu : bUniversity of Hawaii Press, c[2002] 4c©2002  a1 online resource (400 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgments -- tNotes on Translation, Terms, and Quotations -- tIntroduction -- tChapter 1. Sources of Chunqiu Thought -- tChapter 2. Heaven and Man Part Ways: Changing Attitudes Toward Divine Authority -- tChapter 3. The Universal Panacea: Ritual and Preserving Hierarchical Order -- tChapter 4. The World Falls Apart: A Futile Search for International Order -- tChapter 5. When a Minister Mounts the Ruler: Chunqiu Views of Loyalty -- tChapter 6. Nobility of Blood and Spirit: Chunqiu Ethical Thought -- tChapter 7. The Chunqiu Legacy -- tAppendix 1: Grammatical Change in the Zuo: Case Studies of the “Yu” and “Qi” Particles -- tAppendix 2: Zhanguo Data in the Zuo -- tAppendix 3: Comparing Scribal Accounts in the Zuo -- tAppendix 4: Spurious Speeches and Interpolations in the Zuo -- tNotes -- tList of Chunqiu Personalities -- tGlossary -- tBibliography -- tIndex -- tAbout the Author0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis ambitious work focuses on the world of Chinese thought during the two and a half centuries directly preceding and partly overlapping the time of Confucius. Ideas developed by Chunqiu statesmen and thinkers formed the intellectual milieu of Confucius and his disciples and contributed directly to the intellectual flowering of the Zhanguo (Warring States) era (453-221 B.C.E.), the formative period of the Chinese intellectual tradition. This study is the first attempt to systematically reconstruct major intellectual trends in pre-Confucian China. Foundations of Confucian Thought is based on an exploration of the Zuo zhuan, the largest pre-imperial historical text. Relying on meticulous textual and linguistic analysis, Yuri Pines argues that hundreds of the speeches of Chunqiu statesmen recorded in the Zuo zhuan were not invented by the compiler of the treatise but reproduced from earlier sources, thus making it an authentic reflection of the Chunqiu intellectual tradition. By tracing changes in ideas and concepts throughout the Chunqiu period, Pines reconstructs the dynamics of contemporary political and ethical discourse, distilling major intellectual impulses that Chunqiu thinkers bequeathed to their Zhanguo descendants.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066325940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082486257240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824862572423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824862572.jpg  a978-3-11-056414-3  UHP eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-066325-9  University of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  